answers.body_markdown:
Just add the [`javax.servlet` API][1] to the compile time dependencies. You don&#39;t need to include it in the build, it&#39;s already provided by the target servlet container.

Your current pom suggests that you&#39;re deploying to a barebones servlet container ([Tomcat][2], [Jetty][3], etc) instead of a full fledged Java EE application server ([WildFly][4], [TomEE][5], [GlassFish][6], [Liberty][7], etc), otherwise you&#39;d have run into classloading-related trouble by providing JSF along with the webapp instead of using the container-provided one. 

In that case, adding the below dependency should do for a [Servlet 3.1][8] container like Tomcat 8: 

&lt;!-- language: xml --&gt;

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;javax.servlet&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;javax.servlet-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;3.1.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

Or if you&#39;re actually targeting an older [Servlet 3.0][9] container like Tomcat 7, change the `&lt;version&gt;` to `3.0.1` (note: there&#39;s no `3.0` due to a mistake on their side).

If you happen to actually deploy to a [Java EE 7][10] application server like WildFly 8, use the below dependency instead. It covers the entire [Java EE API][11], including `javax.servlet` (and `javax.faces`, so you&#39;d then remove those individual JSF API/impl dependencies):

&lt;!-- language: xml --&gt;

    &lt;dependency&gt;
    	&lt;groupId&gt;javax&lt;/groupId&gt;
    	&lt;artifactId&gt;javaee-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    	&lt;version&gt;7.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

Also here, if you&#39;re targeting an older [Java EE 6][12] application server like JBoss AS 7, change the `&lt;version&gt;` to `6.0`.

### See also: 

- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/65703840/how-to-properly-configure-jakarta-ee-libraries-in-maven-pom-xml-for-tomcat/65704617#65704617

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/servlet/package-summary.html
  [2]: https://tomcat.apache.org
  [3]: https://www.eclipse.org/jetty/
  [4]: https://wildfly.org
  [5]: https://tomee.apache.org
  [6]: httpss://glassfish.java.net/
  [7]: https://www-03.ibm.com/software/products/en/appserv-was-liberty-core
  [8]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax.servlet/javax.servlet-api/3.1.0
  [9]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax.servlet/javax.servlet-api/3.0.1
  [10]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax/javaee-api/7.0
  [11]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/
  [12]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax/javaee-api/6.0

