This case works better when the argument is needed at the start of the JVM, as using `maven-surefire-plugin`, your JVM is already running and the arguments won&#39;t be reloaded (that was my case using some initialization with `@RunWith(SpringRunner.class)` and `@SpringBootTest` to initialize a `MockMvc`).

